It would eventually fail if there's a message.
I have been using as a rule, if the expected is no delievery, it should asserNull(receiveNoWait());
There's already an assertion before on the number of expires.

I don't need that here... I'm already asserting before.
I was just explaining why I prefer using receiveNoWait();
I had some major cleanup on the testsuite weeks ago where I fixed a lot of receive(1000); that was intended to noWait.

